## ---

##

## Residual deviance: 208.31  on 94  degrees of freedom
## AIC: NA
## 
## Number of Fisher Scoring iterations: 5

The poisson model has a smaller P value compared to the quasipoisson model, so the standard poisson model is the best fit

Anova Table

Deviance explained by fine woody debris is 17.165 units, unaccounted deviance is 208.31 and the total deviance (fine woody debris + unaccounted) is 225.47. 7.6% of total deviance is explained by fine woody debris.

Using the Model to Predict Abundance

exp(0.54215+0.26593*1)
## [1] 2.243596
exp(0.54215+0.26593*3)
## [1] 3.818814
exp(0.54215+0.26593*5)
## [1] 6.499986
exp(0.54215+0.26593*100)
## [1] 609040131587

At 100% Fine Woody Debris, the model predicts 609,040,131,587 Bynoes Geckos along a 100m transect. Thank god Australia isnt 100% fine woody debris.
